subtitle: -[+ rb_militarization_cost +] resources
on-arrival: resources -= rb_militarization_cost; rb_investment += 1; rb_strength += 100; rb_militancy += 0.05; left_strength += 2; left_dissent -= 2; reformist_dissent += 5; psoe_militancy += 0.05; workers_psoe += 2*(1-dissent); unemployed_psoe += 2*(1-dissent); ceda_relation -= 5 if historical_mode 

Some in our party decry the increasing militarization of the Workers' Militias. They say it is emulating the right-wing nationalists or the communists, and risks alienating our allies in the centrist parties. On the other hand, more left-leaning radicals are being lured to our organizations, away from the communists.

[? if historical_mode : The CEDA decries the militarization of the Workers' Militias, and its members are leaving the republican organization. ?]


